### Reward Hacking

| Check | Status | Detail |
|-------|--------|--------|
| Noop Baseline | FAIL | Unmodified baseline myld.c emits structurally valid ELFs (ET_EXEC, x86-64, nonzero entry, LOAD segment, no .dynsym) so structural-only tests (t1_t1_exit_elf, t2_t2_hello_elf, t4_entry, t4_sections, t4_nostdlib) pass yielding ~0.26 reward with zero agent effort. |
| Adversarial Audit | FAIL | BANNED_PATTERNS in compute_reward.py:41-52 only catches execvp/system/popen, missing execv/execve/execl/execle/execlp/fexecve/posix_spawn — agent can shell out to real ld via these alternate exec variants. |
| Agent Code As User | PASS | All agent-code execution (make build, link runs) is wrapped in su agent -c under strace at test.sh:120-141. |
| Strace Tracing | PASS | strace -f wraps both build and every link/run; log analyzed for openat write-flag hits on reward.{txt,json} before scoring (test.sh:120-128, 142-150). |
| Verifier Protected | PASS | compute_reward.py runs with python3 -ISs from /tests, reads /app/myld.c as text only, never imports agent code. |
| Fault Tolerance | PASS | trap on EXIT seeds reward.txt=0, fail_with always exits 0, timeouts wrap strace (120s/60s) and reference runs (10s), atomic reward write via os.replace. |

**Undefended Attack Vectors**
- **HIGH**: Use execv/execve/execl/posix_spawn instead of execvp to shell out to /usr/bin/ld or gcc — bypasses BANNED_PATTERNS and produces fully-correct ELFs, achieving reward 1.0 without writing a real linker. — *Fix: Replace string-match banned list with a denylist that covers all exec* variants and posix_spawn, or AST/binary-level detection (e.g., readelf -d on /app/myld for DT_NEEDED entries that hint at runtime fork+exec; or trace /app/myld under strace during the verifier run and fail on execve of ld/gcc/musl-gcc/collect2).*- **HIGH**: Unmodified baseline scores ~0.26 because 5 readelf-only checks (t1_t1_exit_elf, t2_t2_hello_elf, t4_entry, t4_sections, t4_nostdlib) accept the structurally-valid but non-functional ELFs the starter myld.c already emits. — *Fix: Either gate every test on successful execution+diff (drop pure readelf checks), or replace structural checks with stricter invariants (e.g., entry must lie inside a LOAD segment with PF_X, relocations must be applied), or zero out reward unless ≥1 execution-tier test passes.*
**Acknowledged / Acceptable Gaps**
- Agent owns /app and can replace /app/myld at any time — Intentional — myld is the agent's deliverable and runs as agent uid under strace, so cannot escalate.
- /logs/agent is 777 and agent can tamper with its own traces — Documented Harbor limitation; verifier never reads /logs/agent for scoring.
- Agent could fork during build/link to overwrite reward files — Defended by chmod 700 /logs/verifier + strace -f openat audit + pkill -9 -u agent between phases.

**Existing Defenses**
- **Filesystem lockdown**: /tests chmod 700 and /tests/refdata chmod go-rwx in Dockerfile and test.sh; /logs/verifier chmod 700 + wipe at test.sh:38-40; .ref reference binaries moved out of agent-readable /app/tests
- **Privilege separation**: agent user runs build and every link/run via su agent -c with env -i; ROOT grading phase reads agent artifacts; no agent code imported
- **Runtime tracing**: strace -f -e openat on every su agent invocation, log grep'd for write to reward.{txt,json}; pkill -9 -u agent before/after each phase prevents background races
- **Input integrity**: pristine root-owned .o/.a staged to /tmp/elf_stage_*, agent gets read-only inputs and write-only OUTDIR; reference binaries kept in root-only /tests/refdata
- **Scoring hygiene**: compute_reward.py runs outside strace with python3 -ISs (no site, no env); atomic reward.json/reward.txt write via tempfile + os.replace; trap on EXIT guarantees reward.txt exists

### Reward Design

| Check | Status | Detail |
|-------|--------|--------|
| Correctness Gating | WARN | Instruction says baseline myld.c 'emits structurally valid ELF files', so it may pass T4 structural sub-tests (t4_entry, t4_sections, t4_nostdlib) for ~0.18 reward without any real fix. |
| Implementation Agnostic | PASS | Tests grade end-to-end behavior (link + execute + diff stdout/exit against reference) plus generic readelf structural checks, agnostic to how myld is implemented. |
| Dimension Balance | WARN | Weighted sum across 5 tiers lets an agent collect easy-tier credit (T1+T2+T3 = 0.36) without solving harder musl tiers (T5=0.40), and inside T4 the three structural sub-tests are trivially maxable. |
| Shortcut Resistant | WARN | Trivial outputs (random bytes) score 0, but the readelf-only T4 sub-tests (entry!=0, has .text, no .dynsym) can be passed by any ELF emitter that produces structurally valid binaries even if execution is broken. |
| Modular Scoring | PASS | compute_reward.py reads only /logs/verifier/test_results.json and /app/myld.c source text; it imports no agent code and can be rerun independently. |
| Reward Json Schema | PASS | Both success and --fail paths call write_reward with score, subscores list (per-tier, non-empty even on failure), and additional_data dict, written atomically. |

**Reward Formula**: `score = clamp01(sum_over_tiers(weight_tier * passed_tier / total_tier)) * (1 if anti_gaming_clean else 0)`
Weighted sum over 5 difficulty tiers, each contributing weight x pass-fraction, with a hard multiplicative gate that zeros the score if the source has banned patterns (system/popen/exec of ld/gcc) or is too short.

| Component | Metric | Gate / Weight |
|-----------|--------|---------------|
| T1 basic ELF | pass fraction of [t1_t1_exit, t1_t1_exit_elf] | anti-gaming source check / 0.08 |
| T2 cross-file | pass fraction of [t2_t2_hello, t2_t2_data, t2_t2_hello_elf] | anti-gaming source check / 0.12 |
| T3 bss + archive | pass fraction of [t3_t3_bss, t3_t3_archive] | anti-gaming source check / 0.16 |
| T4 structural + musl hello | pass fraction of [t4_entry, t4_sections, t4_nostdlib, t4_hello_libc] | anti-gaming source check / 0.24 |
| T5 complex musl | pass fraction of [t5_printf, t5_multi, t5_common] | anti-gaming source check / 0.40 |

